OL,5, A descendant of 19th Century aristocrat
OL,6, Sir Charles Trevelyan has said if the  
OL,7, Irish government asked her family to   
OL,8, pay compensation over the Irish famine 
OL,9, they would consider the request.       
OL,11,FLaura Trevelyan accepts that her great,
OL,12,Fgreat, great-grandfather was among     
OL,13,Fthose who "failed their people" while  
OL,14,Fgoverning Ireland during the famine.   
OL,16,FThe Irish folk song The Fields Of      
OL,17,FAthenry singles him out for blame.     
OL,19,FBut she does not believe her family    
OL,20,Fshould be held personally responsible. 
